The First Lady, Dr. Jill Biden, visited Fort Liberty in Fayetteville, North Carolina to address military spouses and announce a new executive order to support their economic security. She acknowledged the challenges faced by military spouses, such as leaving behind careers and struggling to find meaningful employment, and emphasized the importance of supporting them. The executive order aims to provide more flexibility, support, and resources for military families, veterans' spouses, caregivers, and survivors. It encourages federal agencies to implement flexible policies, simplifies certification processes for military spouses, and improves access to quality and affordable childcare. The order also focuses on supporting military spouse entrepreneurs and facilitating their business relocation during Permanent Change of Station (PCS) moves. President Joe Biden also spoke at the event, expressing gratitude to the military and recognizing the sacrifices made by military spouses, caregivers, and survivors. He emphasized the administration's commitment to fulfilling its obligation to support them and improve their economic security. The executive order was signed by President Biden and is aimed at strengthening military recruitment and retention, ensuring troop readiness and resilience, and enhancing national security.